Doc# 20220126743 05/19/2022 01:35 PM Page 2 of 3 Lucy Adame-Clark, Bexar County Clerk
EXHIBIT A
5.000 acres of land, more or less, being out of Lot No. Sixteen (16), Block No. Forty-Four (44),
of the San Antonio Suburban Irrigated Farms Subdivision, in Bexar County, Texas, as shown on
a plat filed for record in Volume 0,980, Page 0,125, Bexar County Deed and Plat Records, and
being more fully described by metes and bounds as follows, to-wit:
BEGINNING at a Point located at the Northeast Corner of Lot No. Sixteen (16), Block No.
Forty-Four (44), of the San Antonio Suburban Irrigated Farms Subdivision, in Bexar County,
Texas, in the South Line of the B-12-S Canal for the Northeast comer of this tract;
THENCE with the East Line of Lot No. Sixteen (16), Block No. Forty-Four (44), of the San
Antonio Suburban Irrigated Farms Subdivision, in Bexar County, Texas, South 472.500 feet to a
Point located for the Southeast comer of this tract;
THENCE West 684.000 feet to a Point located in the East Line of the B-12-S Canal for the
Southwest comer of this tract; and,
THENCE with the East Line of the B-12-S Canal, N. 00-13-00 E. 161.100 feet to a Curve, the
length of which being 50.200 feet and the radius of which being 42.000 feet, to a Point located
for a corner of this tract; and, N. 65-27-00 E. 737.200 feet to the PLACE OF BEGINNING.
